00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:40,000
 If you are in covenant relationship with him, it never ceases.

220
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,000
 There's nothing you can do to stop it, nothing you can do to change it.

221
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:47,000
 And David says, "Let's start by praising the Lord, everybody in the different spheres,

222
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:53,000
 because God's a God whose love will never cease, will never stop, because we're in a covenant with him."

223
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:57,000
 What's a covenant? A covenant is very different from a contract.

224
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:01,000
 God says, "I have this very particular love for my people,"

225
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,000
 which would be then the nation of Israel.

226
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:08,000
 If you're a part of the church, you've put faith in Jesus, you are a part of the people of God.

227
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:13,000
 And God says, "You're in a covenant with me, and that covenant means I'll never stop loving you."

228
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:18,000
 If you're a part of his people, I'll never stop loving you, because this isn't a contract.

229
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:23,000
 A contract is you do certain things, and if you do them, or you don't do certain things,

230
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,000
 I don't want you to, then I'll love you.

231
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:28,000
 But if you stop doing those things, or you start doing the things I don't want you to, then I'm out of here.

232
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,000
 That's a contract. God says a covenant.

233
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:34,000
 A covenant says no matter what you do, I will not stop loving you.

234
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:39,000
 I will never stop. You can run, you can hide, but I will not stop loving you.

235
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:44,000
 It's not dissimilar, or really marriage is the clearest example that we have of this.

236
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:50,000
 It's an imperfect one because of so many marriages that just imperfectly reflected,

237
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,000
 but marriage is a covenant.

238
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:57,000
 I remember when I married my wife, and JP did the ceremony,

239
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,000
 and we stood up there, and I looked eyeball to eyeball with my wife, Callie,

240
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:04,000
 wearing this white dress, and we made these insane promises.

241
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:10,000
 We took these vows, and we promised that I will never stop loving you,

242
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:14,000
 for better or for worse. I'm not going anywhere.

243
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:18,000
 If you go crazy, and you run off to Venezuela, I'm coming after you.

244
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,000
 I will never stop loving you.

245
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,000
 That's the promises that you make inside of that covenant.

246
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:26,000
 And she looked at me. It means there were no ifs inside of that.

247
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:31,000
 You never go, "And I vow that as long if, or if you don't do this, then I will."

248
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,000
 Inside of that, it's not conditional. That's what a covenant is.

249
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,000
 I'll never stop loving you.

250
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,000
 And God looks at his people, which is the church, and here the nation of Israel,

251
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,000
 and says, "I'll never stop loving you."

252
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:45,000
 And David says, "Praise the Lord. Here's how we know we can come through,

253
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:50,000
 because no matter what, I can go to sleep at night knowing God loves me

254
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,000
 because I'm a part of his covenant."

255
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:56,000
 He's a covenant-keeping God whose love endures forever.

256
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,000
 He never stops loving you. Never stops loving you.

257
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 David starts by saying, "Let's thank the Lord. He's good. He's rich in love.

258
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,000
 That's not the only reason. We know he will come through."

259
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,000
 Here's what he says, verse 5.

260
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:13,000
 "When I was hard-pressed, I cried to the Lord, and he brought me into a spacious place."

261
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:17,000
 David says, "I was in an overwhelmingly tight place."

262
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:21,000
 You ever felt like you're overwhelmed, anxious, feel like your chest is getting tight?

263
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:25,000
 "I'm in this tight place right now in life. I don't know what I'm going to do about my job,

264
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:29,000
 my finances. I was in this tight place, and what did I do?

265
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:36,000
 I didn't turn to anxiety medication. I didn't turn to substances. I didn't turn to anger.

266
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:40,000
 I turned to you, Lord, and you brought relief," is what David says.

267
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,000
 In other words, in my initial response, which is so foreign for me,

268
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:48,000
 when I get overwhelmed or stressed, I feel like I just get angry.

269
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
 And maybe you can relate to that.

270
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:54,000
 Or maybe you get like just, you just start wailing because you're overwhelmed.

271
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 Maybe you get emotional. Maybe you start turning to alcohol.

272
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:01,000
 I don't know what it is for you, but all of us will turn in our anxiety to something.

273
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,000
 And David says, "Here's what I do. I turn immediately to you, God.

274
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:09,000
 I bring my anxieties to you immediately. I'm overwhelmed, and I go immediately to you.

275
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:12,000
 I'm in this tight place, and I don't turn to any of these other places.

276
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,000
 I turn to you, and I go, 'God, will you help me?

277
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,000
 I'm going to bring the things I'm anxious about to you.'"

278
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 How much of your life would change?

279
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:23,000
 How much more would you be able to exhale if you really did that?

280
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,000
 And I don't know why that's so hard for us when we get anxious,

281
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,000
 and I'm like, "Man, I'm just really worried about this."

282
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
 And someone will be like, "Well, have you prayed about it?"

283
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:33,000
 "No, I haven't prayed about it. I really enjoy being anxious about this right now."

284
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,000
 Like that, it doesn't make sense at all.

285
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:40,000
 We wouldn't even say that, but it's like, "Of course, I should pray about it,

286
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,000
 but for some reason, that's not my knee-jerk response."

287
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
 And David says, "Immediately, I'm overwhelmed, and I go to you."

288
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:52,000
 And unlike those things, like alcohol or anger or anything that brings temporary relief,

289
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,000
 which is why we go to Him,

290
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 He says, "I go to you, and you bring lasting, enduring relief

291
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,000
 without other consequences for those other things.

292
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 I turn to you in my anxiety."

293
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:06,000
 He says, verse 6, "The Lord is with me. I will not be afraid.

294
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,000
 What can mere mortals do to me?

295
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,000
 The Lord is with me. He is my helper.

296
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,000
 I will look in triumph on my enemies.

297
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,000
 It is better to take refuge," I love this,

298
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:23,000
 "It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in humans."

299
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:28,000
 "It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in princes."

300
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:33,000
 David describes why he's confident that he can face the world around him,

301
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,000
 and it's not because his confidence is in himself or in his friends

302
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,000
 or in some other person or in his job.

303
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,000
 He says, "My confidence and security is in you.

304
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:44,000
 I'm going to take refuge in you. You are the shelter.

305
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,000
 You're the reason that I can face the world around me

306
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:51,000
 that feels like it's falling apart because I find security and strength in you."

307
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 Our second point tonight introduced in this text

308
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:56,000
 is that God's protection never fails.

309
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:59,000
 God's love for you never stops.

310
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:02,000
 His protection never fails.

311
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,000
 To those who go and seek his protection

312
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,000
 or who will accept his protection, it never fails.

313
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:12,000
 And David identifies why he can face so confidently the world.

314
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,000
 His source of protection are found in you alone, God.

315
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:18,000
 And it's so--I feel like this is so relevant

316
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:21,000
 because it's so easy to do the opposite of what David says,

317
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,000
 where he says, "Hey, look, don't find security in other people,

318
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:28,000
 in yourself, in money, in the way that you look, in any of those things."

319
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,000
 Like, all of us are going to be tempted to find security

320
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:33,000
 in the things that David just listed out, particularly two of them,

321
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,000
 as it relates to a person.

322
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:38,000
 "Don't find security in a person," David says,

323
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:41,000
 "or in princes," he says,

324
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:44,000
 "or in getting married." Like, I don't find my security

325
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,000
 or who I am in dating someone.

326
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,000
 I'm not the person who always has to be dating someone

327
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
 because there's not a me without a her.

328
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,000
 And so I always have to have someone inside of my life,

329
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,000
 some sort of relationship that's going on.

330
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,000
 I'm not going to be defined by whether or not I'm married.

331
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:59,000
 I'm not--I don't find my security in those things.

332
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
 How relevant is that?

333
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,000
 I mean, some of you may need to memorize verse 9.

334
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:08,000
 "It is better to trust in the Lord than to trust in prince,"

335
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,000
 insert "charming" at the end of it,

336
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:13,000
 that I'm not going to find my security

337
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,000
 in a man showing up or in a woman,

338
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,000
 princess, charming, showing up.

339
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,000
 I'm not going to be defined by whether or not I'm married,

340
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,000
 by any of those things.

341
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,000
 "Leave alone, Lord," or where I'm going to find my security.

342
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,000
 I'm going to find my strength.

343
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:29,000
 I'm not going to date to feel loved

344
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,000
 because I'm secure in that I'm loved.

345
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 That's not the reason I'm going to date.

346
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:36,000
 I may date out of the overflow of my relationship with God,

347
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,000
 and I want to make sure that I'm rooted and grounded,

348
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:41,000
 but I'm not going to date or need to have a boyfriend or girlfriend

349
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,000
 just because I don't feel loved,

350
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,000
 and that's the only way I can experience it.

351
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,000
 No, David says that's crazy.

352
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:48,000
 All of those things, if you find security in a person,

353
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,000
 it's going to fail you, but there's one who won't.

354
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
 Or find our security in money.

355
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:56,000
 How easy it is, David, or we experiencedly--

356
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,000
 I know, personally, to find my security in money.

357
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,000
 There's something about where I'm like,

358
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,000
 "Man, if I just have a little bit more in the bank, I just feel.

359
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,000
 The more I have, the more I feel a little bit like,

360
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,000
 'Whew, I can sleep a little bit better at night.'"

361
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,000
 And David would say, "That's crazy.

362
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,000
 There's only one who can give you true security."

363
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:16,000
 Ironically, money, despite how it makes us feel more secure,

364
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:19,000
 is the thing that we print on it,

365
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,000
 "Hey, don't find security in this,"

366
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,000
 or "We don't find security in this."

367
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,000
 You ever think about that?

368
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,000
 Like, think about it.

369
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:28,000
 On the money, we literally print, "In God we trust."

370
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,000
 We don't trust in these little green pieces of paper.

371
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,000
 It's almost like a comical joke, like,

372
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,000
 "In God we trust. Oh, my God.

373
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,000
 And by God, we mean these things."

374
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,000
 And it's like hilarious.

375
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,000
 We find security in this.

376
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:41,000
 It's all of those who fall away in an instant.

377
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:45,000
 There's nothing holding up an economy that's based on opinion.

378
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,000
 All of those can fall away.

379
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:49,000
 But God is the only thing that provides lasting security.

380
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,000
 Trust in Him.

381
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,000
 Confidence or security being found in your looks.

382
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,000
 David would say, "Don't do it."

383
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:56,000
 The way that you appear, your appearance, your external beauty,

384
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:58,000
 all of those things are going to fall away.

385
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:00,000
 If that is the thing where you find security,

386
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,000
 it's going to fail you and let you down.

387
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,000
 We see this.

388
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:06,000
 Thousands of moms within a very short distance of here

389
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,000
 have found their security in the way they look

390
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:11,000
 and they're injecting all kinds of weird things into their body

391
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:15,000
 to hold on to the beauty that they had in their past.

392
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,000
 And it's falling away.

393
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:19,000
 And David says, "Don't hold on or don't be defined.

394
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,000
 Find your security in the way that you look.

395
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,000
 Find it alone in God.

396
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,000
 He's the only thing that will last when the storms come.

397
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 He's the only thing that will last throughout time."

398
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,000
 Finding security in a job or in health.

399
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:33,000
 David says, "I'm going to take refuge in the Lord

400
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,000
 because all of those things can crumble.

401
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,000
 I'm not going to find my confidence in them."

402
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,000
 It's not dissimilar to...

403
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,000
 Have you ever heard of a storm room?

404
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,000
 Have you guys heard of...

405
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:45,000
 Friends from Oklahoma, a storm room or like a storm shelter

406
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,000
 or storm dorms, if you will.

407
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 Storm dorm is actually a company in town.

408
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 There's a guy who goes to Watermark, remember here,

409
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,000
 and he sells these things called storm dorms.

410
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,000
 And they're these like metal boxes.

411
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,000
 That's what they look like right there.

412
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,000
 And inside of a storm dorm,

413
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 it's basically like a box they'll put inside of your house.

414
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,000
 They'll put it in your garage.

415
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,000
 They'll build a home around it sometimes.

416
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,000
 Very common in Oklahoma.

417
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:08,000
 Any Oklahoma people in this room?

418
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,000
 Three of you.

419
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 Oh, man, awesome.

420
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:13,000
 Man, and any...

421
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,000
 Never mind.

422
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,000
 Okay, we'll keep going.

423
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,000
 Inside of Oklahoma,

424
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,000
 they find different houses with this inside of it.

425
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,000
 And so in that, if a storm comes,

426
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,000
 I go inside of that room.

427
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,000
 And here's why.

428
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,000
 Because this is what happens when a storm comes

429
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:27,000
 and the houses around you fall apart.

430
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:31,000
 But those will last in the midst of the storm.

431
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,000
 They stay standing.

432
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,000
 It's a steel box around you

433
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,000
 that can withstand like thousands and thousands

434
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,000
 of pounds of things on top of it.

435
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,000
 And they provide, not only do they stay standing,

436
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,000
 but anyone inside of them, like think about this.

437
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,000
 I just want you to see this.

438
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,000
 Anyone inside of that, anyone that goes inside,

439
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:50,000
 family came out of that.

440
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:53,000
 And that family was protected.

441
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:55,000
 The four-year-old came out of that.

442
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,000
 And the four-year-old, if he had been four feet away

443
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:01,000
 to the left, would not be alive, found protection.

444
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,000
 And the only thing that stays standing,

445
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:06,000
 David says, if you find security

446
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,000
 or you go to anything else to be your protection,

447
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:11,000
 it's going to crumble, but there is one.

448
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:14,000
 And everyone who goes and seeks refuge inside of him,

449
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:17,000
 Jesus, God, will find protection

450
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:20,000
 no matter what storms in life come.

451
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:23,000
 But he alone, like he liked that storm dorm

452
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:25,000
 in the midst of a storm, stays standing

453
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,000
 and everything inside of it is protected.

454
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,000
 God is that same way.

455
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,000
 When all else around us in this world can crumble,

456
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,000
 he won't.

457
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,000
 And David says, go to him, run to him.

458
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:41,000
 In this room, I know very personally,

